{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"type":"links","style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-233-Adding-Delight-to-your-iOS-App","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-240-Increase-Usage-of-Your-App-With-Proactive-Suggestions"]}],"kind":"content"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2014\/219\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14-219-Adopting-Handoff-on-iOS-and-OS-X"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC14","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Adopting Handoff on iOS and OS X"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Handoff allows people to seamlessly move activities between devices and pick up right where they left off. Learn how to save, transfer, and restore user activities in apps of all architectures. See how easy it is to add Handoff support to your iOS and OS X apps to make your user experience even better."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc14-219-adopting-handoff-on-ios-and-os-x"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14"]]},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC14":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc14","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 6, Swift 1.0, iOS 8, macOS 10.10 (Yosemite)."}],"kind":"article","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC14-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC14.jpeg"}],"title":"WWDC14"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2014/219/":{"type":"download","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2014\/219\/","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2014\/219\/"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-240-Increase-Usage-of-Your-App-With-Proactive-Suggestions":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS and macOS can proactively promote your app and data, thereby increasing user engagement. See how adopting a few simple APIs to inform the OS about your app’s capabilities can lead to your app being suggested in various places like the app switcher, on the lock screen, Contacts, and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-240-Increase-Usage-of-Your-App-With-Proactive-Suggestions","title":"Increase Usage of Your App With Proactive Suggestions","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-240-increase-usage-of-your-app-with-proactive-suggestions"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-233-Adding-Delight-to-your-iOS-App":{"title":"Adding Delight to your iOS App","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"iOS contains powerful technologies you can use to make your app truly delightful. Learn how to take your app to the next level with easy-to-implement features such as Handoff and External Display support. Preserve that feeling of magic in your app with pro-tips that combine animations, gestures and layout, while keeping your scrolling smooth, and your code scalable. Dive into the anatomy of a launch to get your app responsive quickly, and learn some great debugging tricks from the pros!","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-233-Adding-Delight-to-your-iOS-App","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-233-adding-delight-to-your-ios-app","role":"sampleCode"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Learn More…","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDC14-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14-Icon.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC14-Icon.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"WWDC14.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC14.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]}}}